.TH "devm_clk_hw_register" 9 "devm_clk_hw_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_clk_hw_register \- resource managed clk_hw_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_clk_hw_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct clk_hw *hw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is registering this clock
.IP "hw" 12
link to hardware-specific clock data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBclk_hw_register\fP. Clocks registered by this function are
automatically \fBclk_hw_unregister\fPed on driver detach. See \fBclk_hw_register\fP
for more information.
